.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1349" width="2000"><media:credit>Anna Moneymaker</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Chris Wright</media:text><media:description type="plain">U.S. Energy Secretary Chris Wright during a panel at the BlackRock Infrastructure Summit, in Washington, D.C., on March 11, 2026.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-03/260315-chris-wright-vl-920a-fee541.jpg" height="1349" width="2000"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Sun, 10 May 2026 14:10:05 GMT</pubDate><title>Energy secretary says White House is open to suspending gas tax amid soaring prices</title><updateDate>Sun, 10 May 2026 15:54:04 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Mithil Aggarwal</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Sun, 10 May 2026 12:30:40 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Love of Diet Coke runs deep for Ishika Gupta, but it was the fear of losing her favorite drink that took the obsession to new heights</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/world/asia/diet-coke-parties-india-aluminum-can-shortage-rcna343993</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/world/asia/diet-coke-parties-india-aluminum-can-shortage-rcna343993</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-diet-coke-rs-8a5491.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Courtesy of Ishika Gupta</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Ishika Gupta&#39;s Diet Coke party.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Ishika Gupta’s Diet Coke-themed party on April 26.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-diet-coke-comp-rs-b0e30f.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Courtesy of Ishika Gupta</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Gupta’s party was a success with Gen Z, who she says are craving more alcohol-free experiences.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Ishika Gupta’s Diet Coke-themed party on April 26.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-diet-coke-5-rs-6aad0d.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1666" width="2500"><media:credit>Courtesy of Ishika Gupta</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Tickets for the party sold out, with around 150 people in attendance.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Ishika Gupta’s Diet Coke-themed party on April 26.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-diet-coke-rs-8a5491.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Sun, 10 May 2026 12:30:40 GMT</pubDate><title>It started as a joke. Now India’s Diet Coke parties are all the rage as shortages hit shelves.</title><updateDate>Sun, 10 May 2026 12:30:40 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dateTimeWritten>Sun, 10 May 2026 22:40:45 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>The Americans evacuated from the deadly hantavirus cruise ship are on their way to the Nebraska Medical Center’s state of the art National Quarantine Unit. It is unclear how many of the Americans, who are all asymptomatic, will end up staying there and for how long. NBC News’ Camila Bernal has the latest.</description><expires>2056-05-10T22:39:49.000+0000</expires><guid isPermaLink="false">wnn_cbe_hantavirus_americans_nebraska_260510</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/video/americans-on-hantavirus-cruise-ship-head-to-nebraska-263076421637</link><media:content url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/wnn_cbe_hantavirus_americans_nebraska_260510/1/abs/index.m3u8" medium="video"><media:credit></media:credit><media:title>Americans on hantavirus cruise ship head to Nebraska </media:title><media:player url="https://www.nbcnews.com/video/americans-on-hantavirus-cruise-ship-head-to-nebraska-263076421637"></media:player><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/1778452779807_wnn_cbe_hantavirus_americans_nebraska_260510_S3_1920x1080-w7w3dc.jpg"></media:thumbnail><media:description type="plain">The Americans evacuated from the deadly hantavirus cruise ship are on their way to the Nebraska Medical Center’s state of the art National Quarantine Unit. It is unclear how many of the Americans, who are all asymptomatic, will end up staying there and for how long. NBC News’ Camila Bernal has the latest.</media:description><media:subTitle type="text/srt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1778452779807_wnn_cbe_hantavirus_americans_nebraska_260510.srt"></media:subTitle><media:subTitle type="text/vtt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1778452779807_wnn_cbe_hantavirus_americans_nebraska_260510.vtt"></media:subTitle></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/1778452779807_wnn_cbe_hantavirus_americans_nebraska_260510_S3_1920x1080-w7w3dc.jpg"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Sun, 10 May 2026 22:39:46 GMT</pubDate><title>Americans on hantavirus cruise ship head to Nebraska </title><updateDate>Sun, 10 May 2026 22:40:45 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Dennis Romero</dc:creator><dc:creator>Marlene Lenthang</dc:creator><dc:contributor>Suzanne Gamboa</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>The Associated Press</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Reuters</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Sun, 10 May 2026 19:19:06 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>The hantavirus outbreak on a cruise that departed from Argentina last month has cast an unwelcome spotlight on Tierra del Fuego, a region well known for its biodiversity and bird-watching, authorities and guides say</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/world/south-america/birders-defend-argentinian-city-avian-paradise-hantavirus-cruise-rcna344389</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/world/south-america/birders-defend-argentinian-city-avian-paradise-hantavirus-cruise-rcna344389</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260510-magellanic-woodpecker-vl-1240p-15956f.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1333" width="2000"><media:credit>Science Photo Library via Reuters</media:credit><media:text type="plain">A Magellanic woodpecker is seen standing on a tree</media:text><media:description type="plain">A Magellanic woodpecker on a tree on South American archipelago of Tierra del Fuego.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260510-White-bellied-Seedsnipe-vl-1253p-72344d.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1333" width="2000"><media:credit>Marc Guyt</media:credit><media:text type="plain">A white-bellied seedsnipe seen outside standing on moss</media:text><media:description type="plain">A Magellanic woodpecker on a tree on South American archipelago of Tierra del Fuego.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260510-andean-condor-vl-1258p-ab434a.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="2001" width="1500"><media:credit>Joel Reyero</media:credit><media:text type="plain">An Andean condor looks over the snow-covered peaks</media:text><media:description type="plain">A Magellanic woodpecker on a tree on South American archipelago of Tierra del Fuego.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260510-juan-petrina-vl-1229p-144bb2.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1333" width="2